/public/docs/attribute/script_cmds_modifier

Format: (Living_Object)->set_attribute("script_cmds_modifier", iValue);

Description:
  The script_cmds_modifier will change the number of commands
  Living_Object can perform without breaking within a script.
  The default 'maximum' number of commands is 20 (in actuality
  the max is about 21).

  The iValue can be set to a negative (to decrease the number
  of commands in one block), or a positive (to increase) value.
  Though any number can be supplied, the script command will
  only consider a thirty point spread (from -15 to +15). This
  correlates to a range of ~5 to ~35 commands in a single
  execution block.
  
  Supplying a 0 will nullify any effect the attribute has,
  though it is recommended to use remove_attribute instead.

